The paper presents a method for segmenting individual trees in forested areas using airborne LiDAR point clouds. This involves processing large amounts of data and using distributed computing for efficiency. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is computer vision (cs.CV) followed by graphics (cs.GR) and robotics (cs.RO) due to the use of LiDAR technology for 3D imaging and segmentation. The paper also discusses the need for efficient processing, which could fall under computer engineering (cs.CE) and distributed computing (cs.DC).
